meanings.definition: (historical) A transliteration of the name of a Mesopotamian king, Iltani, who ruled in Kish.
meanings.english_definition: A transliteration of the name of a Mesopotamian king, Iltani, who ruled in Kish.

examples.sentence: Itin was the successor of Enmebaragesi.
examples.translation: Itinはエンメバラゲシの後継者でした。
